usic and Musical Style\n |publisher  = Harcourt Brace Jovanoich\n |location   = New York\n |isbn       = 0-15-537720-5\n |ref        = harv\n |url-access = registration\n |url        = https://archive.org/details/historyofmusicmu0003ulri\n}}\n\n{{Italy topics}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Music History Of Italy}}\n[[Category:Italian music history| ]]\n[[Category:Italian music|History]]\n", "name_user": "2600:1700:1991:dd0:e91d:97a0:1d22:3637", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Music_history_of_Italy"}
{"title_page": "Thomas & Friends (series 6)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{unreferenced|date=April 2008}}\n{{Infobox television season \n | season_number = 6\n | bgcolour = #4E5395\n | image = Thomas and Friends DVD Cover - Series 6.jpg\n | image_size = 250px\n | caption = DVD cover art\n | country = United Kingdom \n | network = [[Nick Jr. (UK and Ireland)|Nick Jr.]]<br>[[CITV]]\n | first_aired = {{Start date|df=y|2002|09|16}}\n | last_aired = {{End date|df=y|2002|10|21}}\n | num_episodes = 26\n | episode_list = List of Thomas & Friends episodes\n}}\n'''''[[Thomas the Tank Engine & Friends]]''''' is a [[children's television series]] about the engines and other characters working on the railways of the [[Island of Sodor]], and is based on [[The Railway Series]] books written by the [[Wilbert Awdry|Rev. W. Awdry]].\n\nThis article lists and details episodes from the 6th series of the show, which was first broadcast in 2002.\n\nThis series was narrated by [[Michael Angelis]] for the UK audiences, who also re-dubbed only 2 episodes for the US audiences, while [[Alec Baldwin]] narrated the episodes for the US audiences, which was also his last series. 6 were re-dubbed by [[Michael Brandon]] for the US audiences. \n\nMost episodes in this series have 1 title: the American titles are shown underneath.\n\nThe first season produced by [[HiT Entertainment]]. Marked the return series after 4 years without new episodes.\n\n==Production==\n\nPhil Fehrle had taken over as producer from [[David Mitton]] and [[Britt Allcroft]], while [[Angus Wright (producer)|Angus Wright]] had been replaced by Allcroft and Peter Urie as executive producers.\n\nThis was the first series to oversee an introduction of a writing staff, since the stories from ''The Railway Series'' had already been adapted. Staff-written stories had been introduced in [[Thomas & Friends (series 5)|Series 5]], and this practice remains unchanged since then.\n\nAbi Grant served as script editor for the series. <br/>\nStock Footage: This season had the same theme music as [[Thomas & Friends (series 3)|Seasons 3]], [[Thomas & Friends (series 4)|4]], & [[Thomas & Friends (series 5)|5]]\n{{clear}}\n\n==Episodes==\n<onlyinclude>{{Episode table\n|background=#4E5395|overall=|season=|title=|titleT=UK title (top)<hr />Main title (middle)<hr />US title (bottom)|director=||writer=|airdate=|episodes=\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=131\n |EpisodeNumber2=1\n |Title=Salty's Secret\n |DirectedBy=[[David Mitton]]\n |WrittenBy=Robin Kingsland\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|16|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Salty (the dockyard diesel) comes to work on Sodor, but is disappointed that he has to work in the center Island Quarry. Bill, Ben, and Mavis soon find out that Salty has absolutely no trouble moving the Troublesome Trucks. One night, Salty goes to get some sea air and Mavis asks him if he really misses the sea. Salty admits that he does. The next day, Sir Topham Hatt visits Salty and sends him to work at Brendam Docks, much to Salty's delight.\n\n* The episode's events were recreated in [[Thomas & Friends (series 17)#ep409|Away from the Sea]].\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=132\n |EpisodeNumber2=2\n |Title=Harvey to the Rescue\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=Jonathan Trueman\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|17|df=y}}\n|ShortSummary=Harvey the Crane Engine comes to Sodor on trial, but he is shunned by the other engines due to his unusual appearance, making him miserable. But when Percy has an accident with the Troublesome Trucks, Harvey comes to his rescue, earning respect from the rest of the engines, including Percy.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=133\n |EpisodeNumber2=3\n |Title=No Sleep for Cranky \n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Paul Larson\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|18|df=y}}\n |S