{"title_page": "Blocksworld", "text_new": "{{short description|2013 sandbox video game}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title = Blocksworld\n| image = \n| developer = [[Linden Lab]]\n| publisher = Linden Lab\n| platforms = iPad, iPhone, iPod, macOS, Microsoft Windows <ref>{{cite web|url=http://store.steampowered.com/app/642390/Blocksworld/|title=Blocksworld Steam (streaming is no longer available). page|accessdate=September 25, 2017}}</ref>\n| released = iPad: July 26, 2013 \nWindows: September 25, 2017\nmacOS: September 25, 2017\n| genre = [[Sandbox game|Sandbox]]\n}}\n'''''Blocksworld''''' is a physics-based 3D [[Sandbox game|sandbox]] [[video game]] developed by [[Linden Lab]] for the [[iPad]], the [[iPhone]] in July 26, 2013. In September 25, 2017, ''Blocksworld'' was released on [[Steam (software)|Steam]]. \n==Gameplay==\n\nIn ''Blocksworld'', players can build from 3D building blocks that can be combined to construct simple or complex creations. Players can also use \"action blocks\" and a drag-and-drop visual programming tool to add interactivity and gaming to their creations. Examples include drivable cars, flyable jets, and playable games with win/lose conditions, health systems, and other attributes.<ref>{{cite web|last=Frauenfelder|first=Mark|title=Apps for Kids 41: Blocksworld|url=http://boingboing.net/2013/08/16/apps-for-kids-41-blocksworld.html|publisher=boingboing.net|accessdate=22 June 2015}}</ref> \n\nPlayers can play and share their creations with other ''Blocksworld'' players around the world. Virtual coins serve as the [[in-game currency]], which can be either purchased via the in-app shop or rewarded through various community actions such as having creations rated via stars. These coins can be used to buy a variety of themed building sets including original offerings, like Heroes of Aero, City Blocks, and Star Rangers, and \"models\", structures or other creations built by other players.\n\nBlocks are sorted into categories known as blocks, models, \"props\", textures, colors, \"Blocksters\", and action blocks. Certain blocks have a bronze, silver, or gold border around them that symbolizes their perceived rarity. Blocksters are blocks used to represent characters created by players. Action blocks, such as wheels and hinges, perform specific functions to make creations more dynamic or interactive. Other blocks, like props, serve to fit decorative needs.\n\nActions and sounds are behaviors players can use to add function to blocks. They are placed in a panel with infinite space to store all actions needed, although colors, textures, and any sound effect can be placed in the panel as well.\n\nPlayers have the option to purchase \u201cBlocksworld Premium\u201d which grants an infinite supply of various blocks and items, among other things. It features varying prices and ranks; the higher the rank you purchase, the more items you receive. \n\nWhile it was originally introduced as a one time payment, it has since changed to a subscription system.\nOccasionally an error message will be played, this can last anywhere from one week to half a year, if you have played blocksworld you may have experienced this however, it is not specific to one player, it is a universal message, of which the players have dubbed error 505, this message is the Blocksworld developers testing Updates\n\n==Plot==\nDiscovers Blocksworld, his is as a 3D block to as locations, from seasons 1-7, is at {{Start date|2008|8|8}} or {{End date|2012|19|11}}. His a funny congee locations.\n\n==Development==\n\n''Blocksworld'' was initially developed by Swedish [[independent video game]] developer [[Boldai]], which was acquired by U.S.-based [[Linden Lab]] in early 2013.<ref>{{cite web|last=Fahey|first=Mike|title=This Beautiful Blocky Building Toy is Going Global|url=http://kotaku.com/5978792/this-beautiful-blocky-building-toy-is-going-global|publisher=kotaku.com|accessdate=22 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lindenlab.com/releases/linden-lab-acquires-blocksworld-2|title=LINDEN LAB\u00ae ACQUIRES BLOCKSWORLD|last=|first=|date=24 January 2013|work=|access-date=27 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> An earlier version of the game was briefly available in 2012 in Sweden, Iceland, Finland, Denmark and Norway.<ref>{{cite web|title=App Detail \u00bb App Annie Analytics|url=https://www.appannie.com/apps/ios/app/blocksworld-hd/app-ranking/#daily=2013-06-24&type=ranks}}</ref>  However, for the subsequent global release, the game was repositioned as a [[freemium]] offering where players have the option to purchase premium sets and games, additional building objects and pieces, coins, and other upgrades and extras for a small fee.\nThere is occasionally an error message that will play known to players as error 505 of which is officially dubbed by linden  lab, as update testing, official notices on linden lab incorporated\u2019s website\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://play.blocksworld.com/}}{{dead link|date=December 2019}}\n\n{{Portal|Video games}}\n\n[[Category:2013 video games]]\n[[Category:Educational games]]\n[[Category:Emergent gameplay]]\n[[Category:Free online games]]\n[[Category:Indie video games]]\n[[Category:IOS games]]\n[[Category:MacOS games]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Sweden]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2013 sandbox video game}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| title = Blocksworld\n| image = \n| developer = [[Linden Lab]]\n| publisher = Linden Lab\n| platforms = iPad, iPhone, iPod, macOS, Microsoft Windows <ref>{{cite web|url=http://store.steampowered.com/app/642390/Blocksworld/|title=Blocksworld Steam (streaming is no longer available). page|accessdate=September 25, 2017}}</ref>\n| released = iPad: July 26, 2013 \nWindows: September 25, 2017\nmacOS: September 25, 2017\n| genre = [[Sandbox game|Sandbox]]\n}}\n'''''Blocksworld''''' is a physics-based 3D [[Sandbox game|sandbox]] [[video game]] developed by [[Linden Lab]] for the [[iPad]], the [[iPhone]] in July 26, 2013. In September 25, 2017, ''Blocksworld'' was released on [[Steam (software)|Steam]]. \n==Gameplay==\n\nIn ''Blocksworld'', players can build from 3D building blocks that can be combined to construct simple or complex creations. Players can also use \"action blocks\" and a drag-and-drop visual programming tool to add interactivity and gaming to their creations. Examples include drivable cars, flyable jets, and playable games with win/lose conditions, health systems, and other attributes.<ref>{{cite web|last=Frauenfelder|first=Mark|title=Apps for Kids 41: Blocksworld|url=http://boingboing.net/2013/08/16/apps-for-kids-41-blocksworld.html|publisher=boingboing.net|accessdate=22 June 2015}}</ref> \n\nPlayers can play and share their creations with other ''Blocksworld'' players around the world. Virtual coins serve as the [[in-game currency]], which can be either purchased via the in-app shop or rewarded through various community actions such as having creations rated via stars. These coins can be used to buy a variety of themed building sets including original offerings, like Heroes of Aero, City Blocks, and Star Rangers, and \"models\", structures or other creations built by other players.\n\nBlocks are sorted into categories known as blocks, models, \"props\", textures, colors, \"Blocksters\", and action blocks. Certain blocks have a bronze, silver, or gold border around them that symbolizes their perceived rarity. Blocksters are blocks used to represent characters created by players. Action blocks, such as wheels and hinges, perform specific functions to make creations more dynamic or interactive. Other blocks, like props, serve to fit decorative needs.\n\nActions and sounds are behaviors players can use to add function to blocks. They are placed in a panel with infinite space to store all actions needed, although colors, textures, and any sound effect can be placed in the panel as well.\n\nPlayers have the option to purchase \u201cBlocksworld Premium\u201d which grants an infinite supply of various blocks and items, among other things. It features varying prices and ranks; the higher the rank you purchase, the more items you receive. \n\nWhile it was originally introduced as a one time payment, it has since changed to a subscription system.\nOccasionally an error message will be played, this can last anywhere from one week to half a year, if you have played blocksworld you may have experienced this however, it is not specific to one player, it is a universal message, of which the players have dubbed error 505, this message is the Blocksworld developers testing Updates\n\n==Development==\n\n''Blocksworld'' was initially developed by Swedish [[independent video game]] developer [[Boldai]], which was acquired by U.S.-based [[Linden Lab]] in early 2013.<ref>{{cite web|last=Fahey|first=Mike|title=This Beautiful Blocky Building Toy is Going Global|url=http://kotaku.com/5978792/this-beautiful-blocky-building-toy-is-going-global|publisher=kotaku.com|accessdate=22 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lindenlab.com/releases/linden-lab-acquires-blocksworld-2|title=LINDEN LAB\u00ae ACQUIRES BLOCKSWORLD|last=|first=|date=24 January 2013|work=|access-date=27 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> An earlier version of the game was briefly available in 2012 in Sweden, Iceland, Finland, Denmark and Norway.<ref>{{cite web|title=App Detail \u00bb App Annie Analytics|url=https://www.appannie.com/apps/ios/app/blocksworld-hd/app-ranking/#daily=2013-06-24&type=ranks}}</ref>  However, for the subsequent global release, the game was repositioned as a [[freemium]] offering where players have the option to purchase premium sets and games, additional building objects and pieces, coins, and other upgrades and extras for a small fee.\nThere is occasionally an error message that will play known to players as error 505 of which is officially dubbed by linden  lab, as update testing, official notices on linden lab incorporated\u2019s website\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://play.blocksworld.com/}}{{dead link|date=December 2019}}\n\n{{Portal|Video games}}\n\n[[Category:2013 video games]]\n[[Category:Educational games]]\n[[Category:Emergent gameplay]]\n[[Category:Free online games]]\n[[Category:Indie video games]]\n[[Category:IOS games]]\n[[Category:MacOS games]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Sweden]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n", "name_user": "202.93.153.246", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blocksworld"}
{"title_page": "ToonMarty", "text_new": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name = ToonMarty\n| image = \n| caption = \n| genre = [[Adventure film|Adventure]]<ref name=screener>{{cite web|url=http://tvlistings.zap2it.com/tv/toonmarty/EP02667363?aid=zap2it|title=ToonMarty|work=[[Screener (website)|Screener]]|accessdate=May 17, 2017}}</ref>\n| creator = {{Plainlist|\n* Robin Balzano\n* Pascale Beaulieu\n* Paul Stoica\n* Fr\u00e9d\u00e9rick Wolfe\n}}\n| based_on = {{based on|An original idea|Robin Balzano<br>Pascale Beaulieu<br>Philippe Daigle<br>St\u00e9phanie Larrue<br>Alexis Rondeau<br>Paul Stoica<br>Claudine V\u00e9zina<br>Fr\u00e9d\u00e9rick Wolfe}}\n| developer = {{Plainlist|\n* Sylvie Rochon\n* Madeleine Levesque\n* Craig Martin\n* Lienne Sawatsky\n* Dan Williams\n}}\n| writer = {{Plainlist|\n* Lienne Sawatsky (Head Writer)\n* Dan Williams (Head Writer)\n* Paul Stoica\n* Kevin Shustak\n* Heidi Foss\n* John Hazlett\n* Shawn Kalb\n* Penelope Lawrence\n* Anne-Marie Perotta\n* Gerard Lewis\n* Tean Schultz\n* Sean Scott\n* James Braithwaite\n* Stephen Senders\n* Dave Dias\n* Lisa Hunter\n* Shane Simmons\n}}\n| director = Sean Scott\n| voices = {{Plainlist|\n* Erin Agostino\n* [[Brian Froud (actor)|Brian Froud]]\n* [[Holly Gauthier-Frankel]]\n* Mike Paterson\n* Brett Schaenfield\n}}\n| theme_music_composer = Mathieu Dubus\n| composer = {{Plainlist|\n* Mathieu Lafontaine\n* Leon Louder\n}}\n| country = Canada\n| language = English, French\n| num_seasons = 1\n| num_episodes = 20 (40 segments)\n| list_episodes = #Episodes\n| executive_producer = \n| producer = {{Plainlist|\n* Ghislain Cyr\n* Madeleine L\u00e9vesque\n* Luc Wiseman\n}}\n| runtime = 22 minutes (11 minutes per segment)\n| company = Sardine Productions\n| distributor = [[Corus Entertainment]]\n| network = [[Teletoon]]\n| picture_format = [[HDTV]] [[1080i]]\n| audio_format = [[Stereophonic sound|Stereo]]\n| first_aired = {{Start date|2017|5|1}}\n| last_aired = {{End date|2017|5|25}}\n| website = https://www.teletoon.com/en/tv/toonmarty\n| production_website = \n| image_alt = \n}}\n\n'''''ToonMarty''''' is an [[Animated series|animated]] children's [[television series]] produced by Sardine Productions,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/tv/nickelodeon-takes-toonmarty-on-international-spree|title=Nickelodeon Takes \u2018ToonMarty\u2019 on International Spree|author=Mercedes Milligan|work=[[Animation Magazine]]|date=July 12, 2016|accessdate=May 17, 2017}}</ref> which first premiered on [[Teletoon]] in Canada, on May 1, 2017.<ref name=youtube>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oydLXTKbFFo|title=ToonMarty <nowiki>|</nowiki> NEW Show Coming to TELETOON May 1st at 5PM ET/PT!|author=[[Teletoon]]|work=[[YouTube]]|date=April 12, 2017|accessdate=May 17, 2017}}</ref>{{Better source|reason=Video on Teletoon's official YouTube account. There must be a more reliable source for this.|date=May 2017}}\n\n==Plot==\n''ToonMarty'' follows the adventures of Marty, the mascot of ToonMart who becomes alive when a billboard is hit by lightning. Together, he and his friends Burnie and Holly have fun in Toonville under the supervision of Marty's boss, Jack.\n===ToonMart Marty=== \n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Toonmart Marty\n| genre                    = Pilot design\n| opentheme                = We is a Great ToonMart Toon!\n| endtheme                 = We is a Great ToonMart Toon! (instrumental)\n| num_seasons              = 7\n}}\n===Marty and Burnie's Show=== \n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Marty and Burnie's First Show\n}}\n\n\n==Characters==\n===Main===\n* Marty (voiced by [[Brian Froud (actor)|Brian Froud]]) is the mascot of ToonMart and its only employee.\n* Burnie (voiced by Mike Patterson) is Marty's best friend.\n* Holly (voiced by [[Holly Gauthier-Frankel]]) is a female blue robot.\n* Jack (voiced by Brett Schaenfield) is Marty's boss.\n\n===Recurring===\n* Suki (voiced by Erin Agostino) is Marty's love interest. She is a blue-haired anime [[magical girl]].\n* Carly is a cat.\n* Burnatron is Burnie's father.\n* Super Simon is a superhero who saves Toonville.\n* Chef and Chicken\n* Hobo Jeb\n* Grizelda is a witch. \n* Punchy McKnuckles is Toonsville's bully. \n* Lenny is a bench.\n* Dr. Smarty Pants (Voiced by [[Stacey DePass]] of ''[[Sidekick (TV series)|Sidekick]]'' fame) is a monkey doctor.\n\n==Production==\n{{Empty section|date=May 2017}}\n\n== Broadcast ==\n''ToonMarty'' debuted on [[Teletoon]] in Canada on May 1, 2017.<ref name=\"youtube\" />{{Better source|reason=Video on Teletoon's official YouTube account. There must be a more reliable source for this.|date=May 2017}} In Latin America debuted on [[Nickelodeon (Latin America)|Nickelodeon]] on May 6, 2017. In Poland debuted on [[Nickelodeon (Poland)|Nickelodeon]] on June 1, 2017. In United Kingdom debuted on [[Nicktoons (UK and Ireland)|Nicktoons]] on 9 September 2017 and [[CITV]] on 4 April 2018. In Greece, it is being broadcast on [[Nickelodeon (Greece)]], In Asia debuted on [[Nickelodeon (Southeast Asia)]]. \nIn France, it is being premiered May 1, 2017 on [[Nickelodeon (France)|Nickelodeon]]. In Belgium, it is being premiered June 6, 2017 on [[La Trois]] (OUFtivi).\n\n==Media information==\nAn online game was available on [[Teletoon]]'s website called ''Marty's Special Delivery''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.teletoon.com/en/games/toon-marty/toonmarty-martys-special-delivery|title=MARTY'S SPECIAL DELIVERY|work=[[Teletoon]]|accessdate=May 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table |background=#00a8a8 |overall= |title= |director= |writer= |aux2= |aux2T=Storyboards by |airdate= |airdateR=<ref name=screener/> |episodes=\n\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1a\n| Title           = Moonlighting Marty\n| DirectedBy      = Sean Scott\n| WrittenBy       = Dan Williams\n| Aux2            = Alexei Kazakov\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2017|5|1}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 00a8a8\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| 